/**
 * @mainpage TTDevice Reference Example
 *
 * This document presents the reference design for \b TTDevice — the base layer
 * facade and lifetime manager for a single Tenstorrent device.
 *
 * TTDevice is the primary class that the workload layer (Chip/Cluster) interacts
 * with for per-device operations. All hardware-specific behavior is delegated
 * to the component interfaces provided by TTDeviceModel at construction time.
 *
 * The API surface and delegation pattern shown here represent the target design.
 * Individual methods may still undergo minor refinements, but the overall
 * structure is established and intended to remain stable.
 *
 * \b Contents:
 * - <b>TTDevice API</b> — full doxygen-rendered API documentation.
 * - <b>Source Listing</b> — the header and implementation as clean code.
 *
 * For the component interface specifications (DeviceProtocol, DeviceFirmware,
 * IoWindow, etc.), see the <em>UMD Base API Components</em> document.
 */
